## Common Pitfalls to Avoid

**Top Rejection Reasons:**
1. Inappropriate or insufficient statistics
2. Over-interpretation of results
3. Poorly described methods
4. Small or biased samples
5. Poor writing quality
6. Inadequate literature review
7. Unclear figures/tables
8. Failure to follow reporting guidelines

**Writing Quality Issues:**
- Mixing tenses inappropriately
- Excessive jargon or undefined acronyms
- Missing transitions between sections
- Inconsistent notation

